A tiny jQuery plugin, with minimal [semantic] markup, for generating hardware accelerated webkit transition accordions, ideally suited for iOS web apps.

Usage

$('ul').accordion();

<ul>
	<li><a href="">Your link title</a>
		<p>Your content.</p>
	</li>
	<li><a href="">Your link title</a>
		<p>Your content.</p>
	</li>
</ul>



Issues/bugs

- CSS line-height currently has to be taken into consideration
- Uses ontouchstart mobile webkit event
- Does not use live event queries
- The initial 'collapse' of the list is a visible transition


To-do

- Add other vendor transition prefixes
- Calculate line-height and add to height values
- Allow for click events for desktop usage
- Add :target selector support for RESTful url usage
- Add support for ordered and definition lists